Known IDL3 Parser Bugs
======================

Basic Types:
------------
o) unsigned long long


User Defined Types:
-------------------
o) Recursive Types via struct
o) unions


Constants:
----------
o) const long double
o) const wchar WCHAR_CONST = L'c';
o) const fixed<9,2>	FIXED_CONST = 3.14D;
o) const Color ENUM_CONST = red;


Misc:
-----
o) forward declarations (struct, Iface, component, home, etc.)

o) relative scope declarations



Things that should be checked:
------------------------------

o) Identifier of operations, attributes, interfaces etc. should be check to avoid
	doubles.
	
o) 	Identifiers that differ only in case within the same scope are illegal
	 (e.g. "aName" vs. "Aname")

o) Check identifiers by inherited interfaces, components and homes.	

